The method for baking {flavour} muffins is as follows. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees farenheit. Line a muffin tray wih paper muffin cases. In a medium bowl whisk the milk, butter, and eggs together until well combined. in a small bowl combine the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add the flour mixture to the ingredients and stir until just combined. Gently stir in the {flavour} pieces. Devide the batter evenly between the muffin cases. You can sprinkle the top with sugar if you like. Then bake for 20 minutes. When cooked, transfer the muffins to a wire rack to cool completely.
